snippet.textDisplay: I've been taking testosterone to treat a medical condition for many years now, and one of the byproducts of this is that I don't cry anymore, I can get emotional, but no tears come out; sometimes I feel completely trapped in my emotions, even when the rational thing to do would be to let go .... anyway .. here we are, and I am in a difficult and emotional situation in my life and listened to this song, and Master Saleem's voice instantly brings me to tears especially starting 2:53. The grief and sadness is not pleasant, but I am thankful to be able to let these tears stream down my cheeks finally. It's horrible to have to hold everything inside. Thank you to these beautiful voices. Thank you! 🙏
